&lt;b&gt; We are currently enrolling adult participants ages 18-30 in a research study using computer tasks and questionnaires. Participants control how much money they earn through computer games. &lt;/b&gt;

 

&lt;b&gt;Study visit involves: &lt;/b&gt;

one, hour session at Howell Hall on UNC’s North Campus
filling out surveys
Earn $10 and up from playing games on a computer
 

The purpose of the study is to better understand response to monetary reward!

&lt;b&gt;Please feel free to email (RADstudy@unc.edu) or call (919-843-2346) if you are interested in participating! We look forward to hearing from you!&lt;/b&gt;

This study titled "Neural Correlates of Reward Learning and Cognitive Control Over Rewarding Stimuli" has been reviewed by the UNC-CH Institutional  Non-Biomedical Review Board; IRB Study # 16-0247; Approved 9/7/17
